verbs.description: unpark (third-person singular simple present unparks, present participle unparking, simple past and past participle unparked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) to remove (a car or other vehicle) from a parked position
examples: Tuesday Mrs. Jennie Anderson, 366 North Ninth West St., received the ten-day-old letter asking her to go to Seattle and unpark the car.

entries.meaning: (intransitive) to remove a car or other vehicle from a parked position
examples: A small portion of that area near the sentry booth was left open for vehicular movements essential to parking and unparking.

entries.meaning: (computing, transitive) To release from the fixed position adopted when not in use.
examples: to unpark the head of a disk drive
